Privacy Policy — Soon
Privacy Policy for Soon

Last updated: 11th February 2026

Soon is designed to help you track expiring items and reduce wasted money.
Your privacy is extremely important to us.

1. Information We Collect

Soon stores data only on your device unless explicitly stated.

We may collect:

Item details you enter (title, expiry date, value, notes)

Usage information needed to calculate savings totals

Anonymous diagnostic data provided by Apple (crash logs, performance)

We do not collect:

Personal identity information

Email addresses

Location data

Contacts

Financial account information

2. How Your Data Is Used

Your data is used solely to:

Display your tracked items

Calculate money saved and items used

Send local expiry reminders on your device

All reminders are generated locally using Apple’s notification system.

3. Data Storage

All item data is stored locally on your device using Apple’s secure storage.

We do not operate servers and do not sell or share data.

If iCloud sync is added in the future, this policy will be updated.

4. Third-Party Services

Soon relies only on Apple-provided services:

TestFlight

App Store

Apple crash diagnostics (anonymous)

These services are governed by Apple’s privacy policies.

5. Your Rights

Because data is stored locally:

Deleting the app deletes all stored data

You can manage notifications in iOS Settings

6. Children’s Privacy

Soon does not knowingly collect data from children under 13.

7. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy.
Updates will appear on this page with a revised date.

8. Contact

For questions:

Email: rnkilmurray@gmail.com
App: Soon
